 Butterworth - A 19-year-old Butterworth learner is expected in court on Monday after he was arrested by Butterworth Police for stabbing another learner over school food. The incident apparently happened on Thursday at Zangwa Village, Butterworth. "It is alleged that the suspect stabbed another 19-year-old schoolboy with a spoon on Thursday, at about 12h30, inside the high school premises at Zangwa Village, Butterworth," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "It is alleged that the suspect stabbed the victim for school food as the learners were given their lunch." He said that the 19-year-old learner was taken to Butterworth hospital and later transferred to one of the East London hospitals. "The 19-year-old suspect has been charged with attempted murder. He is due to appear before the Butterworth Magistrate’s Court on Monday, on a charge of attempted murder." Capt Manatha said that the violent behaviour of the suspect has been strongly condemned by the Butterworth Cluster Commander, Brigadier Ngangema Xakavu. Butterworth SAPS Cluster Commander, Brigadier Ngangema Xakavu, wished the injured leaner a speedy recovery. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  